      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 29. March 83. ¶ T. F. Bride Esq. L.L.D. &amp;c ¶ Principal Librarian of the public Library, ¶ Melbourne....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.03.29c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Bride</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">83-133, unit 119, VPRS 805/P inward registered correspondence, VA 913 Public Library of Victoria,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; text-indent: 0.493in; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; text-indent: 0.493in; "
               xml:lang="en">29. March 83.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. F. Bride Esq. L.L.D. &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Principal Librarian of the public Library,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me, dear Dr Bride, to submit to you herewith a letter, received to day by the French mail, by which letter the Publishing Establishment of Th. Fischer in Cassel offers according to byefollowing Index<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's letter is accompanied by T. Fischer<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to M, 14 February 1882 (1883?)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 82-02-14a),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and a handwritten list of publications and prices.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to supply additions to the series of works, acquired by the trustees of the public Library through purchase from the Cassel establishment after the International Exhibition of Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1880-1. See M to M. Irving, 27 March 1881;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>H. Sheffield to M, 6 April 1881<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 81-04-06a);<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and R. Curtis to M, 13 April 1881.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have no doubt, that — if a somewhat extensive order was given — a considerable reduction in the prices would be made.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">This is however the whole correspondence I have on this subject, beyond an incidental expression in one of Mr Fischer's letters to me, that he could furnish considerable addenda to the important works, which the public Library already secured from his issues.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to T. Bride, 9 May 1883<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 83-05-09a);<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>T. Bride to M, 29 August<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1883 (in this edition as 83-08-29a);<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to T. Bride, 30 August 1883; and T. Bride to M, 26 September 1883<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 83-09-26a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I avail myself of this opportunity of thanking you for your Kindness of allowing me on several recent occasions the loan of Books for my studies for some days from your grand establishment. Let me add, that I could offer for your acceptance still 25 or 50 copies of the index to L. sp. pl. first edition,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. M's index to Linnaeus's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Species plantarum</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B80.04.04).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>if you have any use for this little publication while interchanges between your and other institutions are going on. The first part of the Census of Australian plants<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B83.03.04.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has also recently appeared, so that doubtless the Victorian Government will place the usual 25 copies at your disposal, and so it will be likely in the Mines Department, where the second decade of the Veg. fossils<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B82.11.04.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is just got ready</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Very regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
